{"ts":"2026-07-06T08:03:12.744Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/458\n\n## Problem\n`pm claim`/`pm start-task` reject --assignee (unknown_option) while pm update accepts it; agents naturally model claiming as assigning and try --assignee first. The recovery message lists where --assignee IS valid (create, list, list-all) but never points to --author, the actual claim-identity flag — a failed mutation in the critical path.\n\n## Proposed fix\nEither accept --assignee as an alias for --author on claim/release/start-task/pause-task (documented equivalence), or keep the contract strict and make the recovery message for these commands say: use --author <agent> for claim identity; use pm update --assignee for assignee metadata. Alias preferred per never-block routing precedent (2026-05-28 agent-UX pass).\n\n## Definition of done\n--assignee on lifecycle ownership commands either works or produces a targeted recovery hint naming --author; spec covers both commands; contracts/docs updated. Related: GH-444 item (global author ergonomics), pm-gdi7 (error suggestions)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-qfte"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-458: claim/start-task reject --assignee with an untargeted recovery hint (alias or better hint)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Dogfood GH-458: lifecycle ownership commands take --author while update takes --assignee; agents try --assignee first and the recovery message never mentions --author. Duplicate check: 2026-05-28 never-block pass predates this; no open overlap."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:cli","gh-issue"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-06T08:03:12.744Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-06T08:03:12.744Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":60},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"--assignee on claim/release/start-task/pause-task either aliases --author or yields a recovery hint naming --author and pm update --assignee; spec + contracts + docs updated"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-gdi7","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T08:03:12.744Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"08f5de1c79283f71254bf786d9e0e4546159b8a904dba0b95c020016ad9a95b6","message":""}
